<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="505" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/124: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-23T18:00:00-04:00">June 23,
                                    1932—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>42. Referring to the second paragraph of your 98, June 17, 6 p.m.,<note n="18" xml:id="d505fn18">Not printed.</note> what is your estimate
                            of the political situation as it stands at present? Does the present
                            regime give any indication of stability? Is <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> the real power in the Government? What elements
                            are supporting him, what is their strength and to what extent do you
                            think <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> can rely on them?
                            What are the principal elements opposed to him? Are there any
                            developments regarding the possible return of <persName corresp="#p_IGC1">Ibañez</persName>? Your 104 June 20, 8 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d505fn19">Not printed.</note> was protection
                            requested afforded?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>